A former governor of Lagos state, Akinwunmi Ambode, on Saturday revalidated his membership of the All Progressives Congress (APC). This is the former governor’s first public appearance since 2019, The Nation learnt.  Since handing over to Babajide Sanwo-Olu as the governor of Lagos state on May 28, 2019, He has not been seen publicly participating in the party’s activities.  Ambode who was welcomed by teeming supporters, participated in the APC revalidation exercise His reemergence at Epe ward A did set many tongues wagging.